INSTALLATION
************
How to install & run slimrat



RPM-based distro's
==================

RPM (though currently outdated) are available at:
    http://rpm.pbone.net/index.php3?stat=3&search=slimrat&srodzaj=3



Arch Linux
==========

You can install Slimrat from AUR:
    http://aur.archlinux.org/packages.php?ID=20499



Gentoo
======

Step 1: Install Layman
	- Run the following commands (If layman is not already installed)
	- NOTE: Only run the first command, if the git use flag is not enabled.
	The subversion use flag is also recommended for layman. You can remove
	it if subversion is not needed.

	echo "app-portage/layman git subversion" >> /etc/portage/package.use
	emerge layman

Step 2: Add the Custom Overlay
	- Open /etc/layman/layman.cfg
	- Find the line that says "overlays  :
	  http://www.gentoo.org/proj/en/overlays/layman-global.txt"
	- Add http://belak.sbboard.com/gentoo/overlay.xml
	- Sample code:
	  overlays  : http://www.gentoo.org/proj/en/overlays/layman-global.txt
	              http://belak.sbboard.com/gentoo/overlay.xml
	- Run the following commands as root (using either sudo or su)
	  layman -S
	  layman -a belak.gentoo

Step 3: Install slimrat
	- NOTE: For the first command, you may use ** in place of ~x86 to use
	the "hard mask", which draws files right from the repositories. This
	does require subversion. A hard mask will not update automaticly.
	
	echo "net-misc/slimrat ~x86" >> /etc/portage/package.keywords
	emerge slimrat

NOTE: Overlays will not update themselves. You must run layman -S,
along with emerge --sync to update all ebuilds, then run your update



Manual installation
===================


Dependencies
------------

1) Main
  - Perl
  - wget
  - xclip (optional, handles GUI clipboard extensions)

Install these using your package manager of choice.


2) Perl modules
  - Getopt::Long
  - LWP::UserAgent
  - Term::ANSIColor
  - WWW::Mechanize
  - Gtk2::GladeXML (GUI)
  - Gtk2::SimpleList (GUI)
  - Spiffy (GUI)

a) On Debian/Ubuntu
    aptitude install libwww-mechanize-perl
    aptitude install libgtk2-gladexml-perl xclip libspiffy-perl # (GUI)
b) On FreeBSD
    portinstall -Pp ftp/wget devel/p5-Getopt-Long devel/p5-Term-ANSIColor x11-toolkits/p5-Gtk2 x11-toolkits/p5-Gtk2-GladeXML x11-toolkits/p5-Gtk2-Ex-Simple-List www/p5-LWP-UserAgent-Determined www/p5-WWW-Mechanize
c) Manually (through CPAN)
    perl -MCPAN -e 'install Getopt::Long, LWP::UserAgent, Term::ANSIColor, WWW::Mechanize';
    perl -MCPAN -e 'install Gtk2::GladeXML, Gtk2::SimpleList, Spiffy'; # (GUI)


Installation
------------

1) Unpack the tarball at a place you want to. Users wanting to run slimrat do not
   need to have write access to that folder.
    tar -xjvf slimrat-x.x.x.tar.bz2 -C /usr/local/bin/

2) Create symlinks to the main slimrat executables.
    ln -s /Path/to/SlimRat/slimrat /usr/local/bin/slimrat
    ln -s /Path/to/SlimRat/slimrat-gui /usr/local/bin/slimrat-gui

3) Optional: create a system-wide configuration file at /etc/slimrat.conf, a sample
   configuration file documenting all options is provided under the name "slimrat.conf"



Windows
=======

NOTE: the GUI is currently not available on Windows.

Dependencies
------------

1) Main
  - Perl
    http://strawberryperl.com/
  - wget
    http://www.christopherlewis.com/WGet/WGetFiles.htm


2) Perl modules
  - Getopt::Long
  - LWP::UserAgent
  - Term::ANSIColor
  - WWW::Mechanize

    perl -MCPAN -e "install Getopt::Long, LWP::UserAgent, Term::ANSIColor, WWW::Mechanize"


Installation
------------

1) Unpack the tarball at a place you want to, you can use Winrar to open the archive.

2) Open up the "slimrat" executable and replace the 'wget' invocation
       my $command = 'wget '
   to a 'wget.exe' invocation
       my $command = 'wget.exe '

NOTE: configuration files are currently also unavailable on Windows, so you'll need to
      specify any options through the command-line.

